{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ab5cd51b-69c9-423a-a76a-090a52b2e381","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but it depends on `Domain.fs` types.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01U1sDNAeEPduPggWVLmHKdq","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-db5ad0d93df642fb8719c73c55418a17/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-db5ad0d93df642fb8719c73c55418a17/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"6f85b2cb-35ae-40c6-84c4-92b5edac701f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"781E:2C454F:EFE6E:12BCF8:69F549F6"},"id":"f5980dd1-f6f2-4893-859a-1c92175d5a3c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:01.249Z","parentId":"1bd78509-2440-4773-a14e-970a34716f24"}
